                  <abstract>
                     <p>I sit in my study, looking out of the window into the huge maple tree in the front yard. The leaves, jostling against winged russet and lime-green seedpods, have that slightly dusty, used look which presages their decline and fall. The white sky glimmers behind them. They move constantly in a light August breeze.</p>
